cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Phenoscribe, please cite it using this metadata."
title: "Phenoscribe: Automated HPO phenotype coding from patient interviews"
abstract: >-
  Phenoscribe turns French GP-patient audio interviews into Human Phenotype
  Ontology (HPO) codes. It transcribes on-device, pseudonymises PII, extracts
  symptoms with an LLM, shortlists HPO candidates from a local vector index,
  and selects codes with an LLM judge that flags low-confidence matches for
  clinician review.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Jamoulle
    given-names: Tarik
version: 0.1.0
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/tarikjamoulle/phenoscribe"
keywords:
  - human phenotype ontology
  - HPO
  - phenotyping
  - clinical natural language processing
  - speech to text
